<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:Violation occurs when the code uses memcmp to compare a null-terminated C string (boundary) with bytes read from the input buffer. For example, process_value_to_boundary and find_boundary call memcmp with the 'boundary' pointer (which is derived from a C string and for which blen is strlen(boundary)). Using memcmp on such null-terminated strings to perform string comparisons violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.14 (memcmp shall not be used to compare null terminated strings). A concrete scenario: receiving multipart data whose boundary is the C string "myboundary" (blen == strlen("myboundary")), the code uses memcmp(&buf[newline + 4], boundary, blen) to detect the boundary — this is memcmp comparing bytes from a null-terminated string and thus violates the rule.
</scenario>
